# Studio Chrono — environment variables

# --- Database (Postgres / Neon) ---
# Sign up free at https://neon.tech (or use Vercel's built-in Postgres on
# the Storage tab of your Vercel project — it's powered by Neon under the hood).
# Paste the connection string they give you. Looks like:
#   postgresql://USER:PASS@HOST.neon.tech/DBNAME?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL=""

# --- Basic-auth gate (locks the app behind a password in production) ---
# Leave EMPTY for local dev so you can hit the app without typing a password.
# In prod, set this to a long random string. Visiting the app then prompts for
# username + password — username can be anything, password must match this.
ADMIN_PASSWORD=""

# --- Email (Phase 2) ---
# Once Resend is set up, paste the API key here.
# RESEND_API_KEY=""
# RESEND_FROM="receipts@studiochrono.com"
# RESEND_REPLY_TO="joe@studiochrono.com"

# --- AI (Gemini) — payment screenshot extraction + watch ref-# lookup ---
# Get a free key at https://aistudio.google.com → "Get API key"
# Free tier covers Joe's volume. Used for: extracting customer/payment from
# Mercury PDFs/screenshots and looking up watches by reference number.
GEMINI_API_KEY=""

# --- Mercury banking API (optional, for direct Mercury connection) ---
# Get a token at Mercury Settings → API → Create token (read-only is fine).
# Without this, Joe drops Mercury screenshots/PDFs manually (still works).
# MERCURY_API_KEY=""
